#- 
§0Hey dol! merry dol!§0
§0ring a dong dillo!§0
§0
§0Ring a dong!§0
§0hop along!§0
§0fal lal the willow!§0
§0
§0Tom Bom,§0
§0jolly Tom,§0
§0Tom Bombadillo!
#- 
§0Hey!§0
§0Come merry dol!§0
§0derry dol!§0
§0My darling!§0
§0
§0Light goes§0
§0the weather-wind§0
§0and the feathered starling.
#- 
§0Down along§0
§0under Hill,§0
§0shining in§0
§0the sunlight,§0
§0
§0Waiting on the doorstep for the§0
§0cold starlight,
#- 
§0There my§0
§0pretty lady is,§0
§0River-woman's daughter,§0
§0
§0Slender as the willow-wand,§0
§0clearer than§0
§0the water.
#- 
§0Old Tom Bombadil water-lilies bringing§0
§0
§0Comes hopping§0
§0home again.§0
§0Can you hear§0
§0him singing?
#- 
§0Hey!§0
§0Come merry dol!§0
§0derry dol!§0
§0and merry-o,§0
§0
§0Goldberry,§0
§0Goldberry,§0
§0merry yellow§0
§0berry-o!
#- 
§0Poor old Willow-man, you tuck your§0
§0roots away!§0
§0
§0Tom's in a§0
§0hurry now.§0
§0Evening will§0
§0follow day.
#- 
§0Tom's going§0
§0home again§0
§0water-lilies bringing.§0
§0
§0Hey!§0
§0Come derry dol!§0
§0Can you hear§0
§0me singing?
#- 
§0Hop along,§0
§0my little friends,§0
§0up the Withywindle!§0
§0
§0Tom's going§0
§0on ahead§0
§0candles for§0
§0to kindle.
#- 
§0Down west§0
§0sinks the Sun:§0
§0soon you will§0
§0be groping.§0
§0
§0When the night-shadows fall, then the door§0
§0will open,
#- 
§0Out of the window-panes§0
§0light will§0
§0twinkle yellow.§0
§0
§0Fear no§0
§0alder black!§0
§0Heed no§0
§0hoary willow!
#- 
§0Fear neither§0
§0root nor bough!§0
§0Tom goes on§0
§0before you.§0
§0
§0Hey now!§0
§0merry dol!§0
§0We'll be waiting§0
§0for you!
#- 
§0Hey! Come derry dol! Hop along, my hearties!§0
§0
§0Hobbits!§0
§0Ponies all!§0
§0We are fond§0
§0of parties.§0
§0
§0Now let the fun begin! Let us sing together!
#- 
§0Now let the§0
§0song begin!§0
§0Let us§0
§0sing together§0
§0
§0Of sun, stars,§0
§0moon and mist,§0
§0rain and§0
§0cloudy weather,
#- 
§0Light on the§0
§0budding leaf,§0
§0dew on§0
§0the feather,§0
§0
§0Wind on the§0
§0open hill,§0
§0bells on§0
§0the heather,
#- 
§0Reeds by the§0
§0shady pool,§0
§0lilies on the water:§0
§0
§0Old Tom Bombadil and the River-daughter!
#- 
§0O slender as a willow-wand!§0
§0O clearer than§0
§0clear water!§0
§0
§0O reed by§0
§0the living pool!§0
§0Fair River-daughter!
#- 
§0O spring-time and summer-time, and spring again after!§0
§0
§0O wind on§0
§0the waterfall,§0
§0and the leaves' laughter!
#- 
§0Old Tom Bombadil§0
§0is a merry fellow;§0
§0
§0Bright blue§0
§0his jacket is,§0
§0and his boots§0
§0are yellow.
#- 
§0I had an§0
§0errand there:§0
§0gathering water lilies,§0
§0
§0green leaves§0
§0and lilies white§0
§0to please my§0
§0pretty lady,
#- 
§0the last ere§0
§0the year's end§0
§0to keep them§0
§0from the winter,§0
§0
§0to flower by§0
§0her pretty feet§0
§0till the snows§0
§0are melted.
#- Each year at summer's end§0
§0I go to find§0
§0them for her,§0
§0
§0in a wide pool,§0
§0deep and clear,§0
§0far down Withywindle;§0
§0
§0there they open§0
§0first in spring§0
§0and there they§0
§0linger latest.
#- 
§0By that pool long ago I found the River-daughter,§0
§0
§0fair young Goldberry sitting in the rushes.§0
§0
§0Sweet was her§0
§0singing then, and her§0
§0heart was beating!
#- 
§0And that proved well for you - for now§0
§0I shall no longer§0
§0go down deep§0
§0again along the forest-water,§0
§0
§0not while the year§0
§0is old. Nor shall§0
§0I be passing
#- 
§0Old Man Willow's§0
§0house this side§0
§0of spring-time,§0
§0not till the merry spring, when the River-daughter§0
§0dances down the withy-path to bathe§0
§0in the water.
#- 
§0Ho!§0
§0Tom Bombadil,§0
§0Tom Bombadillo!§0
§0
§0By water,§0
§0wood and hill,§0
§0by the reed§0
§0and willow,
#- 
§0By fire,§0
§0sun and moon,§0
§0harken now§0
§0and hear us!§0
§0
§0Come,§0
§0Tom Bombadil,§0
§0for our need§0
§0is near us!
#- 
§0Old Tom Bombadil§0
§0is a merry fellow,§0
§0
§0Bright blue§0
§0his jacket is,§0
§0and his boots§0
§0are yellow.
#- 
§0None has ever§0
§0caught him yet,§0
§0for Tom, he is§0
§0the master:§0
§0
§0His songs are stronger songs,§0
§0and his feet§0
§0are faster.
#- 
§0Get out, you old Wight! Vanish in the sunlight!§0
§0
§0Shrivel like the§0
§0cold mist, like the§0
§0winds go wailing,§0
§0
§0Out into the§0
§0barren lands far§0
§0beyond the mountains!
#- 
§0Come never here again! Leave your barrow empty!§0
§0
§0Lost and forgotten be, darker than§0
§0the darkness,§0
§0
§0Where gates stand for ever shut, till§0
§0the world is mended.
#- 
§0Wake now§0
§0my merry lads!§0
§0Wake and§0
§0hear me calling!§0
§0
§0Warm now§0
§0be heart and limb!§0
§0The cold stone§0
§0is fallen;
#- 
§0Dark door is§0
§0standing wide;§0
§0dead hand is broken.§0
§0
§0Night under Night§0
§0is flown,§0
§0and the Gate§0
§0is open!
#- 
§0Hey! now!§0
§0Come hoy now!§0
§0Whither do you wander?§0
§0
§0Up, down,§0
§0near or far,§0
§0here, there§0
§0or yonder?
#- 
§0Sharp-ears, Wise-nose,§0
§0Swish-tail§0
§0and Bumpkin,§0
§0
§0White-socks§0
§0my little lad,§0
§0and old§0
§0Fatty Lumpkin!
#- 
§0Tom's country§0
§0ends here:§0
§0he will not pass§0
§0the borders.§0
§0
§0Tom has his§0
§0house to mind,§0
§0and Goldberry§0
§0is waiting!
#- 